GLB (Gateway Load Balancer) is an AWS load balancer that operates at Layer 3 (Network Layer) of the OSI model. 
It is specifically designed to deploy, scale, and manage third-party security virtual appliances — such as firewalls, intrusion detection systems (IDS), and deep packet inspection tools — transparently in your network traffic path.

📌 Simple Analogy:
Think of GLB like a Security Checkpoint at an Airport 🛡️

Every passenger (network packet) MUST pass through security screening (firewall/IDS)
Security staff (3rd party appliances) inspect every bag (packet)
Only cleared passengers (safe traffic) board the plane (reach the application)
Passengers don't know the checkpoint exists — it's transparent
